. Join Method Kya Hai?

join() method ka use ek thread ko dusre thread ka kaam complete hone ka wait karane ke liye hota hai.
Matlab, agar Thread A ko Thread B ka wait karna hai, toh hum B.join() likhenge. Tab tak Thread A ruk jayega jab tak Thread B khatam nahi ho jata.

2. Syntax
threadName.join();              // waits until thread finishes
threadName.join(milliseconds);  // waits for given time or until thread finishes

3. Real Life Example

Socho ki aap khana bana rahe ho:

Sabzi katni hai (Thread 1)

Gas pe pakani hai (Thread 2)

Par roti tab tak nahi banegi jab tak sabzi nahi ban jaati. (Thread 3 waits for Thread 2)

join() kaam yahi karta hai — ek thread dusre ka kaam complete hone ka wait karega.

4. Practical Example
class MyThread extends Thread {
    private String taskName;

    public MyThread(String taskName) {
        this.taskName = taskName;
    }

    @Override
    public void run() {
        try {
            for (int i = 1; i <= 5; i++) {
                System.out.println(taskName + " - step " + i);
                Thread.sleep(1000); // har step ke beech 1 second ka gap
            }
            System.out.println(taskName + " completed!");
        } catch (InterruptedException e) {
            System.out.println(taskName + " interrupted.");
        }
    }
}

public class JoinExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) throws InterruptedException {
        MyThread thread1 = new MyThread("Thread 1 - Data Loading");
        MyThread thread2 = new MyThread("Thread 2 - Processing");
        MyThread thread3 = new MyThread("Thread 3 - Report Generation");

        thread1.start();
        thread1.join(); // Main thread wait karega jab tak Thread 1 complete nahi hota

        thread2.start();
        thread2.join(); // Thread 2 complete hone ka wait

        thread3.start();
        thread3.join(); // Thread 3 complete hone ka wait

        System.out.println("All tasks completed! Main thread exiting.");
    }
}

5. Output Example
Thread 1 - Data Loading - step 1
Thread 1 - Data Loading - step 2
...
Thread 1 - Data Loading completed!
Thread 2 - Processing - step 1
Thread 2 - Processing - step 2
...
Thread 2 - Processing completed!
Thread 3 - Report Generation - step 1
...
Thread 3 - Report Generation completed!
All tasks completed! Main thread exiting.

6. Key Points

join() ek thread ko wait karwata hai dusre thread ke khatam hone tak.

Agar join(time) use kare, toh vo maximum utna hi wait karega.

InterruptedException handle karna zaroori hai, kyunki thread wait ke beech interrupt ho sakta hai.

7. Use Cases

Sequential execution in multi-threading.

Data dependency tasks – jaise file load hone ke baad hi processing karni ho.

Task chaining – ek kaam complete hone ke baad hi next kaam start ho.
